{"about_the_game":"Split is a first-person puzzle game with the unique mechanics of creating copies of yourself and manipulating time. The gameplay combines many different types of puzzles from more and less famous puzzle games and takes them to a whole new perspective.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitPuzzle.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>After the recent war, engineers from Epsilon Energy created the Split indestructible shield system. It was to protect individual giant cities covering almost the entire planet from armed conflicts. Different cities have different policies for their citizens. In West Ulrage, every citizen gets a guardian robot at birth. In Hal'Tor, pairs of robots raise several children each. Whereas in Dievez, people are raised in large centers. Most jobs have been taken over by machines. People work mainly as mechanics, programmers, or operators.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitStory.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>The Split control panel is riddled with numerous traps that will require both good reflexes and composure. You can try to destroy enemies or escape from them by using time manipulation and your own clones to distract them.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitFight.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>The game's design refers to Brutalism, an architectural style popular around the 1970s. It was promoted, among others, by the game &quot;Control&quot;. We mixed this style with the digital environment from &quot;Tron: Legacy&quot;. The levels are full of nooks and crannies, which may seem empty at first glance, but lead to interesting places.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitExplore2.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>We were inspired by games such as:<br>Q.U.B.E.2\u201d, \u201cThe Talos Principle\u201d, \u201cThe Turing Test\u201d, \u201cPortal\u201d, \u201cThe Witness\u201d and \u201cAntichamber\u201d<br><br>","achievements":{"highlighted":[{"name":"Initialize","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/3c9015122be96d456168e8303c3f62b261e4f5d3.jpg"},{"name":"Ka-boom","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/cf9f011055fcbd1d5bd3d841c6f3cefd870be23e.jpg"},{"name":"First look","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/053a2b0b7a2497daf5ef10db267fa45ce3afb3ac.jpg"},{"name":"But Our Ending is in Another Castle! ","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/dfe9ee984f5ee12149a5da3d785a8913478810e0.jpg"},{"name":"Chapter Two was not an end of the game","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/a466293132e7fddbeb7573abca335345c5b23560.jpg"},{"name":"First time","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/27084ffe5f8b2cdfc2017bd63339106c5808862b.jpg"},{"name":"According to plan","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/9c6978f700a8fbe143faba7f7a36eaf36ef24808.jpg"},{"name":"Second life...","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/e0f080a065910024f76030d8dc32bd240f8a2912.jpg"},{"name":"Clones!","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/03bb4b403d9ba180c009c1783c34e51067c9242d.jpg"},{"name":"Pause or break","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/743380/a087156c11cd33d3d5c5ae2ae108d7cd0c2a66a9.jpg"}],"total":15},"background":"https://store.akamai.steamstatic.com/images/storepagebackground/app/743380?t=1716962719","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/page_bg_raw.jpg?t=1716962719","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1716962719","capsule_imagev5":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/capsule_184x69.jpg?t=1716962719","categories":[{"description":"Single-player","id":2},{"description":"Steam Achievements","id":22},{"description":"Steam Trading Cards","id":29},{"description":"Steam Cloud","id":23},{"description":"Steam Leaderboards","id":25},{"description":"Family Sharing","id":62}],"content_descriptors":{"ids":[],"notes":null},"demos":[{"appid":1760380,"description":""}],"detailed_description":"<h1>Our best games</h1><p></p><br><h1>About the Game</h1>Split is a first-person puzzle game with the unique mechanics of creating copies of yourself and manipulating time. The gameplay combines many different types of puzzles from more and less famous puzzle games and takes them to a whole new perspective.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitPuzzle.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>After the recent war, engineers from Epsilon Energy created the Split indestructible shield system. It was to protect individual giant cities covering almost the entire planet from armed conflicts. Different cities have different policies for their citizens. In West Ulrage, every citizen gets a guardian robot at birth. In Hal'Tor, pairs of robots raise several children each. Whereas in Dievez, people are raised in large centers. Most jobs have been taken over by machines. People work mainly as mechanics, programmers, or operators.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitStory.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>The Split control panel is riddled with numerous traps that will require both good reflexes and composure. You can try to destroy enemies or escape from them by using time manipulation and your own clones to distract them.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitFight.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>The game's design refers to Brutalism, an architectural style popular around the 1970s. It was promoted, among others, by the game &quot;Control&quot;. We mixed this style with the digital environment from &quot;Tron: Legacy&quot;. The levels are full of nooks and crannies, which may seem empty at first glance, but lead to interesting places.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/extras/SplitExplore2.gif?t=1716962719\" /><br><br>We were inspired by games such as:<br>Q.U.B.E.2\u201d, \u201cThe Talos Principle\u201d, \u201cThe Turing Test\u201d, \u201cPortal\u201d, \u201cThe Witness\u201d and \u201cAntichamber\u201d<br><br>","developers":["GamePlanet"],"genres":[{"description":"Action","id":"1"},{"description":"Adventure","id":"25"},{"description":"Casual","id":"4"},{"description":"Indie","id":"23"}],"header_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/743380/header.jpg?t=1716962719","is_free":false,"linux_requirements":[],"mac_requirements":{"minimum":"<strong>Minimum:</strong><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>OS:</strong> Mac OSX 10.12<br></li><li><strong>Processor:</strong> Intel Core i5-750 or equivalent<br></li><li><strong>Memory:</strong> 4 GB RAM<br></li><li><strong>Graphics:</strong> Nvidia GPU GeForce GTX 660 / AMD GPU Radeon HD 7870<br></li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 6 GB available space<br></li><li><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> Game is is still in development, minimum system requirements may change.</li></ul>","recommended":"<strong>Recommended:</strong><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>OS:</strong> Mac OSX 10.12<br></li><li><strong>Processor:</strong> Intel Core i5-4440S 2.80GHz or equivalent<br></li><li><strong>Memory:</s